# CI/CD Setup Checklist

Use this checklist to ensure your CI/CD pipeline is fully configured and operational.

## Phase 1: Initial Setup ⚙️

### GitHub Repository Configuration

- [ ] **Secrets Configuration** (Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions)
  - [ ] `KUBECONFIG_STAGING` or `RENDER_DEPLOY_HOOK_STAGING`
  - [ ] `KUBECONFIG_PRODUCTION` or `RENDER_DEPLOY_HOOK_PRODUCTION`
  - [ ] `STAGING_API_URL`
  - [ ] `STAGING_WEB_URL`
  - [ ] `PRODUCTION_API_URL`
  - [ ] `PRODUCTION_WEB_URL`
  - [ ] `SLACK_WEBHOOK` (optional but recommended)
  - [ ] `SNYK_TOKEN` (optional but recommended)
  - [ ] `MAIL_SERVER`, `MAIL_PORT`, `MAIL_USERNAME`, `MAIL_PASSWORD` (optional)
  - [ ] `DEPLOYMENT_NOTIFICATION_EMAIL` (optional)
  - [ ] `PREVIEW_DEPLOY_TOKEN` (optional, for preview deployments)

### GitHub Environments

- [ ] **Create `staging` environment**
  - [ ] No protection rules (auto-deploy)
  - [ ] Set environment URL: `https://staging.trading-bot.example.com`

- [ ] **Create `production-approval` environment**
  - [ ] Add required reviewers (at least 1-2 team members)
  - [ ] No wait timer needed

- [ ] **Create `production` environment**
  - [ ] Add required reviewers (senior team members)
  - [ ] Optional: Add 5-minute wait timer
  - [ ] Set deployment branches: `main` and tags matching `v*`
  - [ ] Set environment URL: `https://trading-bot.example.com`

- [ ] **Create `production-rollback` environment**
  - [ ] Add required reviewers (senior team members)

### Branch Protection Rules

- [ ] **Protect `main` branch** (Settings → Branches → Add rule)
  - [ ] Require pull request before merging
  - [ ] Require 1-2 approvals
  - [ ] Dismiss stale approvals on new commits
  - [ ] Require status checks: `CI Success`, `Security Summary`
  - [ ] Require branches to be up to date
  - [ ] Require conversation resolution
  - [ ] Do not allow bypassing

- [ ] **Protect `develop` branch** (if used)
  - [ ] Require pull request before merging
  - [ ] Require status checks: `CI Success`

## Phase 2: Workflow Customization 🔧

### Update Placeholder URLs

- [ ] Replace `staging.trading-bot.example.com` with your staging URL
- [ ] Replace `trading-bot.example.com` with your production URL
- [ ] Replace `preview.trading-bot.example.com` with your preview URL
- [ ] Update container registry if not using GitHub Container Registry

### Review Workflow Configuration

- [ ] Review `ci-parallel.yml` - Adjust test commands if needed
- [ ] Review `security-scan.yml` - Configure security tools
- [ ] Review `deploy-staging.yml` - Adjust deployment strategy
- [ ] Review `deploy-production.yml` - Adjust deployment strategy
- [ ] Review `preview-deploy.yml` - Configure preview platform

### Optional Integrations

- [ ] Set up Codecov for coverage reporting
- [ ] Configure Datadog/Sentry for monitoring
- [ ] Set up custom quality gates
- [ ] Add performance testing

## Phase 3: Testing 🧪

### Test CI Pipeline

- [ ] Create a test branch: `git checkout -b test/ci-pipeline`
- [ ] Make a small change and commit
- [ ] Push and create PR: `gh pr create`
- [ ] Verify CI workflow runs
- [ ] Check all jobs pass (or expected failures)
- [ ] Verify PR comment with CI summary
- [ ] Verify preview deployment (if configured)

### Test Security Scanning

- [ ] Trigger security scan manually: `gh workflow run security-scan.yml`
- [ ] Check scan results in Actions tab
- [ ] Verify artifacts are uploaded
- [ ] Check for any critical vulnerabilities
- [ ] Verify Slack notification (if configured)

### Test Staging Deployment

- [ ] Merge test PR to main
- [ ] Verify staging deployment workflow starts
- [ ] Check Docker images are built and pushed
- [ ] Verify deployment to staging environment
- [ ] Check health checks pass
- [ ] Verify smoke tests run
- [ ] Check Slack notification (if configured)
- [ ] Verify staging URL is accessible

### Test Production Deployment

- [ ] Create version tag: `git tag v0.1.0`
- [ ] Push tag: `git push origin v0.1.0`
- [ ] Verify production workflow starts
- [ ] Check pre-deployment validation passes
- [ ] Verify Docker images are built with version tags
- [ ] Approve deployment in GitHub Actions
- [ ] Verify deployment to production
- [ ] Check smoke tests pass
- [ ] Verify notifications sent
- [ ] Check production URL is accessible

### Test Rollback (Optional)

- [ ] Trigger a failed deployment (intentionally)
- [ ] Verify automatic rollback triggers
- [ ] Check rollback notifications
- [ ] Verify service is restored

