## Success Criteria 🎯

Your CI/CD pipeline is fully operational when:

- ✅ All secrets are configured
- ✅ All environments are created with proper protection
- ✅ Branch protection is enabled
- ✅ Test CI run is successful
- ✅ Test staging deployment is successful
- ✅ Test production deployment is successful
- ✅ Notifications are working (Slack/Email)
- ✅ Team is trained on processes
- ✅ Documentation is complete and shared
- ✅ Monitoring is in place

## Quick Reference Commands 📝

```bash
# View workflow runs
gh run list

# View specific workflow
gh run list --workflow=ci-parallel.yml

# Trigger workflow manually
gh workflow run security-scan.yml

# View workflow logs
gh run view <run-id> --log

# Re-run failed jobs
gh run rerun <run-id>

# Cancel running workflow
gh run cancel <run-id>

# Create and push version tag
git tag v1.0.0
git push origin v1.0.0

# View deployment status
gh run list --workflow=deploy-production.yml

# Check workflow status
gh run watch
```

